        "dcterms:title": "SHARED-REF INTEGRITY — no silent κ drift: every app's content-addressed _shared reference (`src=\"/.holo/sha256/<hex>\" data-holo-shared=\"<name>\"`) pins the CURRENT bytes of the lib it names. When a canonical _shared lib is edited its κ moves; an app still pinning the old hex then 404s on the κ-route (which re-derives from disk, Law L5) and 409s under the content-verify Service Worker in production — the lib never loads, its global is undefined, and the app throws at runtime with NO build-time error (the failure mode that broke Holo Terms). This witness re-derives κ(name) for every data-holo-shared ref across all served app HTMLs and fails closed on any mismatch, so seal drift goes red at the gate instead of silently dark in the browser. The read-only twin of repin-shared-refs.mjs (the one-command heal); green here ⟺ `repin-shared-refs --check` is clean"
      },
