      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-telemetry",
        "dcterms:title": "OBSERVABILITY PLANE — system-wide telemetry native to the UOR substrate (Holo Telemetry, ADR-0073): adopts the OpenTelemetry data model (Span · Metric · LogRecord · Resource · Scope) and W3C Trace Context as content-addressed UOR objects, and REJECTS the Prometheus central scraper (a long-running server that trusts the emitter — a foreign runtime the substrate forbids). A span IS a PROV-O Activity whose W3C trace-id / span-id are DERIVED from the operation's content, so holding only a signal's κ re-derives its identity (Law L5) and a tampered structural field breaks the id; a trace is a self-verifying PROV-O DAG (each child prov:wasInformedBy its parent under one trace-id); `traceparent` injects in exact W3C form and round-trips (all-zero / malformed ids refused). The HONEST SPLIT: wall-clock measurements (start/end/duration, a measured value) are marked hostel:rederivable=false and host-attested — never claimed as re-derived. No new infrastructure: the κ-store is the collector, graph traversal is the query, Pin/Own is the exporter, the conscience gate is the privacy boundary. Telemetry is LOCAL-ONLY by default; egress requires explicit consent AND passes the conscience gate (Law L1, private-first, fail-closed), then emits genuine OTLP/JSON (OpenTelemetry interop). Auto-wired system-wide by the theme runtime (Law L2, one canonical wire); mint nothing"
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
          "@id": "earl:failed"
        }
