        "dcterms:title": "OBSERVABILITY COMMAND CENTER — Holo Control (the telemetry monitoring & control dashboard, ADR-0073 consumer): models the whole system as a graph (this OS at center, every external interaction a governable edge — app · agent · resource · human · wallet) and stays CALM BY DEFAULT via a robust signal-processing core. This row witnesses that core (tools/holo-control-dsp-witness.mjs, pure + deterministic): a noise floor from median + MAD (a few loud spikes do NOT inflate it and hide the next signal); a robust z-score (a degenerate window does not divide by zero); an EMA low-pass (steady-state) + first-difference high-pass (change); SALIENCE = magnitude × novelty × governance-risk (egress / wallet-out / agent-write weigh heaviest), so ranking surfaces the one thing worth the operator's eyes; thresholding WITH hysteresis (an alert latches at the high gate, releases below the low gate — it cannot flap); an aggregate SNR (the fraction of activity that is genuine signal); and a matched filter for the exfiltration signature (sustained egress to a NEW destination), distinct from a lone spike. The app is additionally render-witnessed in a real browser (tools/holo-control-render-witness.mjs, committed result): it boots, binds the Holo UI tokens, populates REAL edges from the live catalog, ranks/switches/inspects, runs a conscience-gated control action that seals a verifiable receipt, and is HONEST where a feed is unwired (no fabricated flows/balances/presence). Local-first; the dashboard observes and nothing leaves the device unasked"
      },
