      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#app-ui-tokens",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo UI conformance extends from text size to COLOR + SHAPE (ADR-0057) — the canonical palette (--holo-bg/-surface/-ink/-accent/…) and radius (--holo-radius-sm/-/-lg) tokens are the single source, and a hardcoded hex color or px border-radius in an app's authored shell bypasses them. Because color is IDENTITY (apps + the faithful reproductions keep their own colors under the ADOPT-vs-OWN model, ADR-0023), this is a no-regression RATCHET, not a forced rewrite: an app may not add hardcoded themeable values beyond its committed baseline, so the corpus can only get MORE token-conformant. Radius exact-matches (8/12/16px) are adopted as tokens pixel-for-pixel (burndown-app-radius.mjs)"
