      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#app-ux-conformance",
        "dcterms:title": "The Holo UX doctrine (ADR-0062) is strictly adhered to by EVERY holospace application, not just the OS chrome — so every app is beautiful, functional and coherent with the whole OS. Loading the ONE engine every app already loads (holo-theme.js) bootstraps the Holo UX runtime (holo-ux.js), so every app inherits the WHOLE doctrine — the host-OS native feel, the capability tier, the resource budget, the live propagation — by binding one canonical wire (Law L2), with no per-app script tag. This witness proves that inheritance is real for every served app (the carrier is intact + the canonical doctrine object re-derives + every app loads the engine), and holds each app to its OWN-shell obligations: its manifest keeps the plain voice (jargon-free — signal over noise); it honors prefers-reduced-motion through the ONE OS-wide guard every app inherits from holo-theme.css (time/compute/energy held sacred — WCAG 2.3.3, no per-app copy needed, no app may override it with its own !important motion); and its modifier keys are NATIVE-ADAPTIVE — no unconditional Apple-only glyph (⌘/⌥), the host's modifier is derived (HoloPlatform/metaKey) or rendered by the inherited data-holo-shortcut helper (⌘N on macOS · Ctrl+N on Windows/Linux). Read-only over the served app repo — no edits, no re-lock"
      },
