        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-devtools-cdp",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo DevTools — the κ-CDP backend (ADR-0095): the F12 developer environment, native to the substrate and equally usable by humans, AI agents, and Holo Q. The vendored Chrome devtools-frontend is the cheap UI half (a CDP client over a Connection); this is the load-bearing half — a PURE dispatcher that speaks a faithful SUBSET of the Chrome DevTools Protocol where every handle (nodeId · backendNodeId · objectId · requestId) is an ALIAS for a κ, so it is witnessed in Node against the REAL substrate (holo-object + holo-scene) with no browser. DOM domain ⇄ the scene manifest tree (ADR-0089): #document → holo-scene → one holo-object node per placed κ-object, each carrying its κ (Law L1), and the node ⇄ κ map round-trips (backendNodeId ⇄ κ) and RE-DERIVES identically from the content-addressed scene order (Law L1/L5). Network domain = the κ-stream timeline (the differentiator, not HTTP): each requestId IS a κ, and the response carries the substrate columns — axis (sha256/blake3) · found · the L5 verify badge (resolve + verifyDeep) — which goes RED on a tampered κ (re-derivation refuses it, Law L5). Runtime.evaluate is FAIL-CLOSED through the injected conscience (no gate → refused; a blocking gate refuses; an accepting gate routes through Q and seals a PROV-O-shaped receipt — who · verb · effect κ), mirroring Q.agent (ADR-0091, Law L4). ONE backend, THREE doors with no forked logic: humans speak raw CDP (serve) over the cross-frame bus, AI agents call the MCP tool adapter (devtools_query_dom/_inspect/_network/_eval) which returns a self-verifying JSON-LD/UOR envelope (schema.org ⊕ PROV-O ⊕ DID), NOT a raw CDP frame — CDP stays the human door's PRIVATE transport (the §7 T1 resolution that backs the 100%-W3C claim) — and Holo Q calls a first-class inspect verb; all three land on the SAME dispatch. Unmapped methods degrade gracefully (a clean 'unsupported', a faithful SUBSET); repeat inspection of an unchanged κ is stable (the κ-memo IS the cache, Law L3). Witnessed tools/holo-devtools-cdp-witness.mjs (14/14). DESIGN STAGE: this is the backend spine (Bet B); the vendored-frontend mount + transport bind, the remaining domains (CSS/Sources/Memory/Performance/Application), and the dedicated #holo-devtools-conform W3C row are the staged remainder of ADR-0095's 8-stage plan"
      },
      "earl:result": {
