      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-widgets-modes",
        "dcterms:title": "The four preset desktop widget MODES (Focused · Learn · Work · Play) are beautiful, golden-ratio-true compositions wired to REAL holo-native widgets and apps — no mockups, no dead tiles. Each is a curated scene over the Holo Widgets runtime (holo-widgets.js defineScene, {mode:true}); the right-click desktop switch (HoloWidgets.setMode) is NON-DESTRUCTIVE — leaving a mode saves its own per-mode board and the sticky Q voice orb survives every switch (ADR-0088/0089 per-holospace boards). GOLDEN RATIO is the discipline, not decoration: one φ width ladder (hero:secondary:header = φ:φ = 400:247:153) sizes every tile and makes the primary:secondary split φ:1; widgets place on the real golden cuts (the upper line 0.382 and the complementary lower line 0.618, ratio φ) and focal heroes centre on the golden gridline via GPX, never dead-centre; margins are the existing φ³ MARGIN (Play relaxes one φ-step). FOCUSED is truly minimal — one hero (your intention note) on the focal point (0.382), a focus timer on 0.618, the time held quietly; no quote, three tiles, vast calm. LEARN is a φ:1 two-column study space (a reading/notes surface over a sprint timer · resources · Q as a copilot launch tile), distinct from Work. WORK is a workspace — to-do hero + schedule + the machine in the header — with REAL app launch tiles (Files · Code · Wallet, opened by org.hologram id through window.HoloShell.openApp) anchoring the lower-left, the bottom-right kept clear for the orb. PLAY puts the vinyl disc up front on the focal point with roomier margins. The new `launch` widget is the only app surface on the calm board — it opens the live holospace (or summons Q) via the shell's own launcher, no iframe; its label holds the 16px readability floor (ADR-0057, max(--holo-font-min,…)). FIRST BOOT lands first-time users in Focused (seedFirstRun → setMode('focused')). Witnessed tools/holo-widgets-modes-witness.mjs (19/19) — re-derives the φ ladder + golden cuts numerically and source-asserts every scene composes real widgets, the launch tiles open real apps, the switch is non-destructive, and the floor holds."
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
