      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-widgets-snap",
        "dcterms:title": "The Holo Widgets SNAP ENGINE — seamless, delightful, magnetic position anchoring for every object on a holospace tab, powered by interact.js (MIT) vendored UNMODIFIED. Dragging or resizing any widget snaps to (1) SIBLING edges + centres (Figma-style alignment across all objects on the tab), (2) the canvas GOLDEN anchors — the φ gridlines 0.382/0.618, the margins, the centre — and (3) a fine pixel grid; the pull is magnetic within a small range and releases cleanly beyond it (non-sticky). interact.js is THE engine: vendored at /_shared/interactjs/interact.min.js by tools/vendor-interactjs.mjs (the npm tarball pinned by sha512 integrity, Law L5), loaded SAME-ORIGIN (no CDN at runtime, SW-content-verified), driving interact.draggable + resizable + the snap/grid/restrictSize modifiers; positions stay the runtime's own {x,y,w,h} (clampPos bounds, dock/aside/top aware) so the scene manifest + reflow are untouched (ADR-0088/0089). GRACEFUL by construction — the hand-rolled pointer drag stays active (gated by w._snap) when interact is absent or offline, so it always works; tap and double-tap are preserved (interact distinguishes tap from drag). Applies to EVERY widget on EVERY tab and engages from the first frame once interact is ready. ATLAS96 stays the CONTENT coordinate (κ→cell), not a screen grid — the layout grid is a separate, resolution-independent φ lattice (the right tool for pixels). Witnessed tools/holo-widgets-snap-witness.mjs (14/14) — re-derives the nearest-line snap math numerically (magnetic-within-range · null-beyond · sibling+golden targets) and source-asserts the interact.js wiring, the integrity pin, the same-origin load, the gated fallback, and tap/double preservation. (The vendored bundle is a .gitignored content artifact; the witness is bundle-independent.)"
