      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-devtools-bridge",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo DevTools — the vendored-frontend ⇄ κ-backend TRANSPORT BINDING (ADR-0095, Bet A). The κ-CDP backend (#holo-devtools-cdp) proved the substrate half; this proves the OTHER unknown — that the REAL Chrome devtools-frontend, vendored UNMODIFIED (chrome-devtools-frontend@1.0.1645245, tarball pinned by sha512 integrity, Law L5; the built front_end/ is a .gitignored content-addressed artifact fetched by tools/vendor-chrome-devtools.mjs), drives that backend over the Q cross-frame bus with NO fork of the UI. devtools-frontend talks to its embedder through ONE seam, read FROM THE VENDORED SOURCE (not memory): OUT — MainConnection.sendRawMessage → InspectorFrontendHostInstance.sendMessageToBackend(message) (core/sdk/Connections.ts:47); IN — MainConnection subscribes to the host events emitter for DispatchMessage and delivers event.data (Connections.ts:30,52-53; core/host/InspectorFrontendHostAPI.ts Events.DispatchMessage='dispatchMessage'). So holo-devtools-host.mjs installs a globalThis.InspectorFrontendHost whose sendMessageToBackend forwards each CDP frame over the EXISTING holo-privacy:rpc bus (method:'cdp', brokered by holo-gov.js exactly like q.summon/q.remote.*, the caller's identity asserted un-forgeably) to HoloDevToolsServe (holo-devtools-serve.mjs, the twin of HoloQServe) — and re-delivers replies/events as DispatchMessage. CDP stays the human door's PRIVATE transport (ADR-0095 §7 T1). The witness reconstructs MainConnection's EXACT contract and runs it over a mock of the bus (the holo-q-bridge-witness pattern): a CDP DOM.getDocument round-trips the scene tree BY κ, concurrent frames multiplex by id, the Network κ-stream verify badge survives the transport (Law L5), Runtime.evaluate is FAIL-CLOSED end-to-end and routes through Q + seals a receipt when the shell is governed (Law L4), and a malformed frame is refused not crashed. It also asserts the binding targets the real vendored seam, so a version bump that moves it turns RED. Witnessed tools/holo-devtools-bridge-witness.mjs (10/10; committed-result — re-running needs the vendored bundle, like the browser witnesses). PENDING: live-in-browser boot of the full UI (preview smoke), the holo-gov.js 'cdp' branch wired into the live shell, the remaining CDP domains, and the #holo-devtools-conform W3C row"
      },
