        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-devtools-domains",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo DevTools — the REMAINING CDP domains over the κ substrate + the live-shell governance branch (ADR-0095). Bet B proved DOM/Network/Runtime; this extends the κ-CDP backend across the rest of the F12 surface, each mapped to a real substrate fact: CSS — the Styles panel resolves the --holo-* design tokens (ADR-0023/0030) AND surfaces the readability FLOOR (--holo-font-min, ADR-0057) as an un-overridable !important rule (the WCAG / §7 T2 resolution, made visible); Sources — Debugger.getScriptSource returns the source κ's text (publishSource → SoftwareSourceCode, ADR-0055) with the L5 verify badge, SOURCE-by-κ NOT a live V8 debugger (the ADR-0095 §8 honest non-goal); Memory — the HeapProfiler snapshot IS the κ store (node=κ-object · edges=links[] the Merkle-DAG, ADR-0060 · dedup visible: distinctKappa===store size, one κ stored once); Performance — substrate counters (CDP frames · κ resolves · store objects · link edges) with wall-clock HOST-ATTESTED (rederivable=false), never faked (the Holo Telemetry honesty split, ADR-0073); Application — Storage.getUsageAndQuota reports κ-store usage + the live scene. Graceful degradation holds across the larger surface (unmapped → clean 'unsupported', §8). GOV BRANCH: holo-gov.js routes the human DevTools frame's method:'cdp' to W.HoloDevToolsServe (holo-devtools-serve.mjs), FAIL-CLOSED (no authority ⇒ refused) with the caller identity host-asserted via byWin — the design's 'holo-gov.js gains ONE branch' claim, realized and asserted against the real edited file (the same grounding the bridge witness uses on Connections.ts). Witnessed tools/holo-devtools-domains-witness.mjs (9/9, pure-Node, in gate LIVE). PENDING: the HoloDevTools holospace app entry that installs window.HoloDevToolsServe in the live shell, the live-in-browser UI paint (gated on a BUILT bundle — npm ships source, see flow-map §5), and the #holo-devtools-conform W3C row"
