      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-devtools-shell",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo DevTools — the SHELL INSTALL (ADR-0095): the running shell serves CDP to a DevTools holospace frame, 100% SERVERLESS and κ-anchored, with the vendored Chrome UI loaded UNMODIFIED. The only first-party code is the glue — the authority install + the live-scene projection; devtools itself is untouched. holo-devtools-ui.js PROJECTS the live desktop's sealed UOR objects into a string-valued κ-store (Map.get O(1), the κ-memo IS the cache — Law L3) and installs window.HoloDevToolsServe = the κ-CDP backend over BROWSER/SW-SAFE resolve + verifyDeep (no Node Buffer — re-derive the address, identical Law-L5 semantics in browser/SW/Node, Law L2); a tampered κ is refused (the RED verify badge, L5). shell.html imports it beside the other authorities (window.HoloTrinity/HoloMind/HoloQServe), so holo-gov.js routes the DevTools frame's method:'cdp' straight to it (the one branch, fail-closed, byWin identity). The holospace entry holo-devtools.html installs the embedder host shim (globalThis.InspectorFrontendHost) bound to the parent over the holo-privacy:rpc bus (no socket → low latency) BEFORE loading the VENDORED devtools entrypoint (front_end/entrypoints/inspector/inspector.js) — every path same-origin /_shared, no CDN, no WebSocket (100% serverless). Witnessed tools/holo-devtools-shell-witness.mjs (10/10, pure-Node over the guarded install path: browser-safe resolve/verify re-derive + refuse a tamper; installDevToolsServe answers a real CDP DOM.getDocument + Network frame BY κ over the projected store; the shell wiring + the serverless entry are asserted against the real files). HONEST: the vendored UI PAINTS once a BUILT front_end bundle is present — npm ships TypeScript source, so the build/extract is the remaining vendoring step (flow-map §5; Chrome 149 locally is the cheap source). The authority + transport are live and proven now; the pixels await the built bytes."
