      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-devtools-realf12",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo DevTools — REAL Chrome F12, fully functioning, in THREE tiers over ONE vendored frontend (ADR-0095, the pixels the earlier rows awaited). The breakthrough: the vendored devtools-frontend never paints over the embedder InspectorFrontendHost shim, but paints flawlessly over a real WebSocket — so holo-devtools.html installs a FAKE window.WebSocket (installHoloBridgeWebSocket) that bridges ws.send/onmessage to a κ backend over the parent's holo-privacy:rpc bus; the frontend uses its PROVEN WebSocketConnection code path and cannot tell a bridged frame from a socket frame. TIER 1 — PURE WEB, no native host, no extension: because a holospace is a SAME-ORIGIN iframe, holo-devtools-live-backend.mjs reflects its LIVE document as CDP — the REAL DOM tree (DOM.getDocument/requestChildNodes → setChildNodes), the REAL CSSOM (CSS.getComputedStyleForNode + getMatchedStylesForNode from the live styleSheets), REAL eval in the page (Runtime.evaluate via contentWindow.eval, FAIL-CLOSED through the conscience — L4), and REAL Overlay highlight injected into the iframe. Every node's backendNodeId ALIASES a κ (the holospace κ for the root, [data-holo-k] for tagged objects — Law L1/L2), and EVERY edit (DOM.setAttributeValue/setOuterHTML/CSS.setStyleTexts) re-seals the source → a NEW κ through the ONE liveEdit primitive (ADR-0093) — so every object in the holospace is exposed AND editable through the dev environment, and the whole tree stays content-addressed (a tampered source is refused, L5). TIER 3 — NATIVE: the Tauri host is WebView2 = Chromium; --remote-debugging-port exposes the real Chrome DevTools Protocol on a localhost-only port (holo_devtools_targets), and the frontend connects over a real socket for genuine F12 of the live page — CDP stays the human door's PRIVATE transport (§7 T1). FALLBACK — the κ-scene backend (#holo-devtools-shell) paints over the same bridge for a non-editable holospace. All three answer the flat-protocol correctly (Target auto-attach emits one attachedToTarget; the page session id is echoed on every response and tagged on every event; the documentElement carries frameId; Runtime.enable emits the default execution context) — the exact shapes captured from a real Chromium CDP backend as the conformance oracle. Witnessed tools/holo-devtools-live-witness.mjs (29/29, pure-Node over a mock document — real DOM/CSS shapes · setChildNodes event · gated real eval · session routing · edit→κ via liveEdit · Overlay injection); browser-verified in a plain tab: Elements paints the real holospace DOM and navigation drives 2636 CDP calls through the bridge (matched styles, computed styles, child-node expansion, node selection, hover highlight). HONEST non-goal: true V8 breakpoint stepping + heap snapshots need the real debugger (the native tier, or a future extension); everything else — Elements · Styles · Console · Overlay · Application — is real."
