      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-playground",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Playground — every element rendered INSIDE a holo app is a κ-addressed object you can right-click and edit live in the browser, no tooling and no code knowledge required (the Playground 2.0 interaction model — github.com/PlaygroundNow/Playground-2.0, 'bang on the objects and they bang back' — native to κ + the conscience + the Laws). A shell-level edit already reaches whole surfaces (HoloLiveEdit) and widgets; this closes the gap INSIDE the app: a tiny in-frame agent (holo-playground-agent.mjs), injected post-load into every same-origin app frame at the SAME lifecycle as Ambient Q, makes every element right-clickable (Edit source · Edit text · Duplicate · Delete) with an editable glow. OPT-IN, OFF BY DEFAULT: the agent is injected but DORMANT — no hover glow, no right-click hijack, no double-click capture — so a normal app behaves normally; Playground is armed PER SURFACE from the shell's window context menu ('Edit objects (Playground)'), survives a reload (data-pg-active), and is exited from the element menu, Esc, or the on-screen badge. THE ONE EDIT PATH: the agent NEVER seals — it mutates its own live DOM, serialises the host document, and posts the bytes UP; createPlaygroundHost (in the shell) verifies the message came from the actual mounted frame (un-forgeable event.source identity — a srcdoc frame's origin is 'null', so identity not origin string) and routes it to the ONE primitive createLiveEditor.edit (ADR-0093), exactly as the Q chat sidecar and Holo DevTools (ADR-0095) do — no second sealer, no shadow copy. An element edit reseals the WHOLE host surface to a NEW root κ (the surface IS one κ-object; an element is a sub-tree), which RE-DERIVES by content (Law L5). L5-CRITICAL: the agent is injected into the LIVE contentDocument (NOT baked into the sealed srcdoc), and serialise() drops every [data-holo-ephemeral] node (its own UI/script + the ambient Q runtime) and the transient glow class — so the sealed κ === 'user source + user edit' with ZERO injected noise. Content-addressing is preserved (the edit κ === publishSource(source); lineage is recorded as an OUT-OF-BAND prov:Derivation edge, NEVER folded into the κ — that would break the κ-memo), so an identical re-seal is an O(1) no-op. Mutate-in-place: an in-frame edit flags the host to reseal the κ + model only and SKIP the srcdoc reload, so in-app JS state is not reset; the resulting κ is posted back to the frame and flashed as confirmation. Witnessed tools/holo-playground-agent-witness.mjs (19/19, pure-Node over a deterministic DOM, host wired to the REAL HoloRepo.publishSource + the REAL createLiveEditor — the ephemeral strip, one-edit-path/no-sealer, L5 re-derivation, content-address/memo safety, prior→new lineage, mutate-in-place, the origin guard, and the governed door staying fail-closed). Browser-verified: the agent injects into a real same-origin app frame, right-click paints the menu, an edit updates the element in place and the surface κ changes; cross-origin apps degrade honestly (no agent, no crash). STAGE 1 of the staged plan; the inline 'Library' code panel, cell/table blocks, governed in-tab script execution, the process manager, and collaborative docs (on the existing CvRDT — NOT Automerge, Law L4) are the staged remainder."
