      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-bittensor-mcp",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Bittensor (ADR-0071) is usable by AI agents over MCP — bittensor_snapshot · bittensor_agentfacts · bittensor_infer · bittensor_settle are advertised, JSON-Schema'd tools on the canonical Hologram MCP server (tools/list + /.well-known/mcp.json), each returning a SELF-VERIFYING UOR object the agent re-derives (Law L5): an agent maps a subnet's metagraph (a κ-rooted dcat:Catalog pinning the block hash), reads a neuron's dual-trust AgentFacts (NANDA record ⊕ UOR object ⊕ hotkey-signed VC), queries a miner and re-derives the PROV-O inference receipt, and settles TAO against PROVEN work (testnet-gated, tampered work pays nothing) — without trusting any server, and a tampered object is refused through the agent's own verify_object tool. The supply side of the agent economy, agent-callable."
