      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-mind",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Mind PHASE 0 (ADR-0081) — agency is an OS-wide ambient κ-transform, not a single app. The re-derivable core (os/usr/lib/holo/holo-mind.mjs) composes ONE verb surface from the three agent doors that already exist (MCP ADR-0047 · agents ADR-0049 · skills ADR-0035), de-duped and capped; runs the intent → plan → act → seal loop where every step passes the EXISTING fail-closed conscience (ADR-033) before dispatch (a blocked step seals nothing, dispatches nothing — self-discipline as a structural property); and seals each action as a self-verifying PROV-O work receipt (ADR-045 shape) that re-derives byte-for-byte (Law L5) — a human action and an agent action through the IDENTICAL surface sealing the IDENTICAL shape. Identical asks replay O(1) (Law L3); no new store, transport, or trust root (Law L4). Witnessed 8/8 (the loop core is a pure function of injected plan/gate/dispatch, the holo-suspend pattern; the eighth check proves the isomorphic sealer is BYTE-IDENTICAL to the canonical Node envelope). SHELL-WIRED + gate-enforced: os/usr/share/frame/shell.html imports os/usr/lib/holo/holo-mind-ui.js, exposing window.HoloMind whose loop draws its roster from the LIVE doors (window.HoloMCP.descriptor ⊕ /.well-known/skills/index.json), gates every step through window.HoloConscience.evaluate (fail-closed until the constitution self-verifies), and dispatches through window.HoloMCP (the serverless in-page MCP transport) — and this row is required + in gate.mjs LIVE. Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the two new served modules (offline precache + dual-axis anchor — the re-lock cascade, the same build step ADR-0052 defers for Holo Q; until then the SW falls back to network for them, never 409s), and the LEARNING κ-transform (the trace corpus + governed self-evolution, Phase 2). See docs/specs/holo-mind-implementation.md."
