      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-mind-evolve",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Mind PHASE 2 (ADR-0081) — the LEARNING κ-transform: κ(trace-corpus) ⊕ κ(optimizer) → κ(improved-skill), the skill writeback ADR-0035 deferred (\"a deterministic projection, not a mutable store\"), now GOVERNED and re-derivable. The trace corpus (os/usr/lib/holo/holo-mind-evolve.mjs) is an append-only, content-addressed chain — rewriting any PAST trace changes its κ and breaks every successor (Law L5, the AgentTrust hash-linked-chain idiom ADR-0039). A SkillRevision mints a NEW κ linking its parent (prov:wasRevisionOf) and what it derived from (prov:wasDerivedFrom the corpus head ⊕ the optimizer); it is IN FORCE only when EVERY governed condition holds — tests pass · within the size ceiling · conscience accepts · operator-ratified · cooling-off elapsed (mirrors the constitution's own governed succession, ADR-033 rule 4) — and the in-force fact is itself RE-DERIVED from the sealed gate, so a forged inForce over a failing gate is refused; the parent κ is preserved forever (rollback = re-pin the parent). Built on the adaptive-immune-classifier pattern (ADR-033: a learned model as a PURE FUNCTION of a content-addressed corpus) generalized from defense to all competence; the loop's LEARN step appends a trace per run and window.HoloMind.evolve runs the optimizer through the registered model. HONEST BOUNDARY: the optimizer's PROPOSAL is a stochastic LLM generation, NOT reproducible (ADR-0052's non-verifiable mode) — L5 holds over the AUDIT TRAIL (which corpus, which gates, ratified by whom), not the search. Witnessed (tools/holo-mind-evolve-witness.mjs, 10/10). PROMOTED: the trace corpus + the learned skills are DURABLE (write-through to the OS's OWN κ-store — holo-store.js idbBackend over the existing 'holo'/'kappa' IndexedDB, no new infrastructure, Law L4 — hydrated at boot so learning accumulates across reloads and tabs, Law L3), and an in-force revision RE-PROJECTS into the live roster (its SKILL.md frontmatter becomes a roster entry that WINS de-dup, the ADR-0035 writeback) so an evolved skill ACTUALLY CHANGES BEHAVIOR — verified live in a real browser (the corpus head + the learned skill survive a fresh page load; the evolved skill leads the roster). Required + in gate.mjs LIVE."
      },
