      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-factory",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Factory (ADR-0097) — the software factory as ONE verb (Q.factory / window.HoloFactory.run) native to Q. A self-observing SDLC loop (signal → change → verify → seal → learn) that SPECIALIZES Holo Mind (ADR-0081), adding NO substrate (Law L4): the re-derivable core (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-factory.mjs) seals the signal as a holo:Intent (a red check is source 'environment'), retries change→verify up to a budget, and seals a holo:FactoryRun PROV-O activity linking the intent (prov:used) and every attempt's chained holo:ActionReceipt (prov:wasInformedBy) plus the trace (prov:wasDerivedFrom) — the whole DAG re-derives byte-for-byte (Law L5). MODEL-INDEPENDENT by construction (Factory 2.0's router): the change door routes per task — Dream diffusion INFILL (ADR-0083) for a both-sided surgical span, the AR coder for whole-source. The change is applied through the SAME governed liveEdit door (hosc:Edit) when a live surface is mounted, else sealed as a holo:Artifact κ (in-tab, serverless); VERIFY is the injected SDLC oracle (a witness/test) with in-tab floors parse (syntactic, never executes) + rederive (κ integrity). NEVER FAKES GREEN (Law L5): ok is true ONLY when a verifier passed; with none bound it returns the change as an honest unverified PROPOSAL, never a claimed fix (mirrors holo-q-diffusion's report-never-fabricate); a blocked conscience verdict seals nothing and produces no effect (fail-closed, no path skips the gate). SHELL-WIRED into the SHARED agent core: os/usr/lib/holo/holo-mind-ui.js constructs the factory with Holo Mind's OWN durable κ-store + trace-corpus head + window.HoloConscience gate + borrowed model sampler, and persists the advanced corpus head, so the factory and the ambient loop learn into ONE durable memory (Law L3) — exposed as window.HoloFactory + Q.factory. Witnessed 9/9 (tools/holo-factory-witness.mjs: loop converges + stops at green, the run + whole DAG re-derive, never-fakes-green with no verifier, fail-closed on a blocked gate, learns-from-failure into the append-only corpus, the parse oracle accepts valid + rejects broken code, no-fabrication with no brain still seals an honest run, a tampered run is refused, the seal is byte-identical to the canonical Node envelope). Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served module (the re-lock cascade, the same step ADR-0052/0081 defer — until then the SW falls back to network for it, never 409s)."
      },
