      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-factory-tend",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Factory AUTONOMOUS TENDER (ADR-0097) — the self-observing keystone that closes the loop: signal → verified fix, hands-off. The core insight (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-factory-tend.mjs) is that a CHECK is simultaneously the MONITOR and the ORACLE — a red check IS the signal, and re-running that same check on a candidate IS the verification — so auto-signal (#1) and witness-verification (#2) collapse into one object (the witness idiom). The tender runs every registered check; each RED one auto-drives a factory.run whose verifier is that very check; GREEN ones are left untouched (no run, no fabrication); a verified fix is SHIPPED durably through the check's own write(). The OS conformance gate's OWN output ingests as signals: gateChecks() reads the EARL report and turns every FAILED row into a check (proposal mode for a repo-level row that a serverless tab cannot write; bind a browser-runnable witness to close one). DRIVEN ONLY BY USER INTENT (the binding constraint): nothing fires until watch() seals a standing holo:Intent (source 'user'); that intent is the authority every autonomous tend links (prov:used); the conscience gates every change (inherited from the factory — no path skips it); the edge-clock ticker arms only on the user's call and the user stops it — no timer self-arms, no act happens, without the user's intent (Holo Mind's GoalStack + opt-in-scheduler discipline, ADR-0081). The FactoryTend pass seals a re-derivable PROV-O activity (Law L5); NEVER fakes green (a still-red check stays 'unverified', is never written). Witnessed 8/8 (tools/holo-factory-tend-witness.mjs: tend converges a red check to fixed, a green check is skipped with the proposer never called, a verified fix ships durably, a still-red check is never 'fixed' nor written, watch seals a user-source intent every tend links, registering a check + intervalMs 0 arms NO timer and fires nothing until the explicit call, the FactoryTend re-derives, and the EARL report's failed rows become signals while passed rows do not). Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served module (the standing re-lock cascade, deferred across the Mind family — SW network-fallback, never 409s)."
      },
