      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-factory-triage",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Factory SEMANTIC TRIAGE (ADR-0097) — the factory FINDS the target itself, so the user states intent and the factory locates what to fix or watch. A natural-language signal ('the add function is broken', 'keep my notepad working') is embedded by the OS's verified embedder (EmbeddingGemma-300m via HoloVoice.embed, ADR-0096) and matched BY MEANING against the live candidate surfaces — NOT by keyword — closing the gap where the human had to name the target or pass prefix·suffix. The core (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-factory-triage.mjs) is PURE given the injected embed() (the holo-mind injected-faculty idiom — witnessed in Node with a deterministic stub embedder, live in the browser with EmbeddingGemma); ranking is a deterministic cosine over the vectors (ties by id), so triage RE-DERIVES given the embedder. The tender's discover() locates the target(s) and REGISTERS a check for each (a candidate brings its own verify/read/write, else a parse-check over its source), so the autonomous loop tends what the user DESCRIBED with no manual registration. HONEST (Law L5): nothing above the similarity threshold ⇒ NO target — it reports it cannot locate, it does not guess (mirrors never-fakes-green). Wired into holo-mind-ui.js sharing the agent core: window.HoloFactory.locate/discover + Q.factory.locate/discover, and factoryWatch('…intent…', { candidates }) expands the intent into checks before tending. Witnessed 6/6 (tools/holo-factory-triage-witness.mjs: ranks by meaning with ZERO shared words while the unrelated candidate scores ~0; locate returns the best above threshold; nothing relevant ⇒ null + a reason; deterministic; discover registers the located check; and the discovered check, when red, drives a factory fix end to end). Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served module (the standing re-lock cascade, deferred across the Mind family)."
      },
      "earl:result": {
