      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-factory-catalog",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Factory CANDIDATE CATALOG (ADR-0097) — the live enumeration of fixable targets, the last seam between 'locates' and FULLY HANDS-OFF on real holospaces: with the catalog wired, Q.factory.watch('keep my notepad working') finds the surface and closes the loop unattended, no candidates passed. The core (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-factory-catalog.mjs) COMPOSES injected providers (each { list() → candidates }) plus a self-register seam target(id, spec), de-duping by id (explicit targets first — the richest). A candidate is { id, text, read?, write?, lang? }: text is what triage embeds, read is the current source (the brain's context + the parse oracle), write persists a verified fix. Built-ins: liveEditProvider — EVERY live mounted holospace surface (HoloLiveEdit) as a candidate, WRITE through the GOVERNED agentEdit door (conscience default-deny, hosc:Edit receipt) and READ through kRouteResolver (κ → source over the /.holo/sha256/<hex> content-addressed route, Law L5 — the bytes ARE the κ); and listProvider for explicit objects. HONEST (no faked doors): no resolver ⇒ read omitted (the brain proposes from the signal alone, the parse oracle still verifies), no agentEdit ⇒ write omitted. WIRED into holo-mind-ui.js sharing the agent core: the tender builds the catalog from window.HoloLiveEdit + the κ-route; factoryLocate/Discover/Watch fall back to catalog.candidates() when none are passed (hands-off); an app self-registers via Q.factory.target(id, spec). Witnessed 7/7 (tools/holo-factory-catalog-witness.mjs: providers merge + de-dup explicit-first; target() self-registers with read/write; a surface writes through agentEdit + a refusal throws; read resolves κ→source; honest degrade when a door is absent; the κ-route resolver reads bytes + nulls a miss; and triage locates the right target FROM the catalog end to end). Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served module (the standing re-lock cascade, deferred across the Mind family); richer providers (the holospace scene-node + app catalog) layer on the same seam."
      },
      "earl:result": {
