      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#q-fuse",
        "dcterms:title": "Q.fuse (ADR-0098) — a serverless COMPOUND model (the OpenRouter Fusion / pi-fusion 'compound beats components' idea) as ONE more verb on the single door (ADR-0091): run a PANEL of small specialists on the SAME prompt IN PARALLEL → a JUDGE compares them (consensus · contradictions · unique insights · blind spots) → a SYNTHESIZER writes ONE new answer none produced. The lift is the synthesis step and it is MODEL-SIZE-AGNOSTIC — a diverse panel of tiny on-device minds, judged + synthesized, beats any one of them — so the honest framing is 'compound beats components on the WASM floor', NOT 'Fable-5 in a tab'. Adds NO new transport, gate, or store (Law L4): every stage rides the EXISTING κ-memo fabric (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-q-fabric.js, ADR-0084) — content-addressed compute over the durable OS κ-store — so an EXACT repeat fusion is O(1) (zero models run, Law L3) and a NEAR-repeat (swap one panel member) re-runs ONLY the changed leg + judge + synthesis (the unchanged legs are cache hits), where OpenRouter re-pays 5× every call and cannot reproduce a fusion. The whole deliberation seals ONE re-derivable holoq:FusionReceipt (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-q-fuse.js mintFusionReceipt): prov:used = every panel κ tagged by member + the judge κ, prov:generated = the synthesis κ — a single altered byte breaks the address and is refused (Law L5, receipt canonicalization reused from ADR-0090 holo-q-receipt.mjs). ANY generative provider is a panel member, INCLUDING a governed remote one (ADR-0090): a member flagged remote → the fusion seals tier 'hybrid' instead of 'local', a PER-CALL opt-in, never the default. Wired as Q.fuse / Q.configureFuse (holo-q.js); with no panel configured it returns an honest notice and never throws. Witnessed 27/27 (tools/holo-q-fuse-witness.mjs: parallel panel, distinct per-member κs, zero-model exact repeat, single-leg near-repeat, FusionReceipt re-derivation, a tampered receipt refused, the hybrid-tier flip). Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served modules (the deferred re-lock cascade, the same step ADR-0052/0081/0097 defer — SW network-fallback, never 409s)."
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
          "@id": "earl:passed"
        }
      },
      "earl:mode": {
        "@id": "earl:automatic"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "earl:Assertion",
      "earl:assertedBy": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/tools/gate"
      },
      "earl:subject": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os",
        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#q-fuse-panel",
        "dcterms:title": "Q.fuse DEFAULT PANEL (ADR-0098 / ADR-0096) — turn the model registry's brains into the diverse panel + judge + synthesizer Q.fuse consumes, resolving the one honest tension in serverless fusion: real MODEL diversity (≥3 distinct loaded models) is multi-GB and device-gated, while the any-browser warm set is ONE brain. The assembly (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-q-fuse-panel.js defaultPanel) ships TWO modes, LABELLED, never faked: PERSONA mode (the any-browser DEFAULT) — one warm brain, N members differing by REASONING LENS (concise · first-principles · skeptic), diverse PATHS not weights (the self-consistency idea; synthesis still lifts above a single greedy pass), labelled diversity 'persona'; MODEL mode (the upgrade) — when the host supplies ≥2 distinct loaded samplers, each registry model (Coder-1.5B · SmolLM2-360M · a third family) becomes a member, labelled diversity 'model'. With nothing loaded it REFUSES (an empty panel + an honest reason), it does NOT invent a model (Law L5). A (messages,opts)→deltas sampler (the holo-q-codegen.js / holo-voice-llm.mjs shape) is ADAPTED into the fabric's {id, generate(input,opts)} provider with the persona baked into the PROVIDER, so the same question addresses a DISTINCT κ per member — which is what carries diversity through to the synthesis. configureDefaultFuse(Q, {sampler|samplers}) wires Q.fuse in one call; shell.html lights it up the moment a warm on-device brain loads. Witnessed 18/18 (tools/holo-q-fuse-panel-witness.mjs: persona-mode three diverse lenses + judge + synth; the adapter diverges members on the same input; the REAL fuse engine over the default panel yields distinct κs + a verifiable receipt; model-mode from ≥2 samplers; refuse-when-unloaded; configureDefaultFuse wires a door in one call and refuses when nothing is loaded). Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served module (the deferred re-lock cascade); the registry discovery loop choosing the MODEL-mode panel."
      },
