      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "earl:Assertion",
      "earl:assertedBy": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/tools/gate"
      },
      "earl:subject": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os",
        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-recall",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Recall (ADR-0099) — serverless κ-graph retrieval over the PRIVATE corpus as ONE more verb on the single door (ADR-0091): Q.recall. The open-web stack (ADR-0037–0046, Resolve→Federate→Answer→Graph, no-AI, deterministic) answers 'what does the open web know'; this answers 'what do I know' over the user's OWN objects (holospace sources · receipts · notes · the κ-store) and stays STRICTLY separate — a result's provenance always names which universe it came from, the two never silently merge. Adds NO new transport, gate, or store (Law L4): the embedder is the existing on-device one (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-q-embed.js, ADR-0096, content-addressed O(1) cache), rank fusion is the SAME Reciprocal Rank Fusion the open-web federate uses (ADR-0038, score = Σ 1/(k+rank)), the optional synthesis rides Q.fuse (ADR-0098), the gate's verdict seals into the receipt. The WRITE side (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-q-corpus.js) indexes a page ONCE — chunk → embed → BM25 postings → a typed κ-graph built by ZERO-LLM AUTO-LINK (regex entity scan + heuristic edge-typing: cites · derived_from · mentions · authored_by · part_of), every chunk/edge/entity content-addressed so the whole index re-derives (L5) and dedups by content (L3); zero-LLM is the RIGHT call, not a shortcut — a model-extracted graph would vary run-to-run (an L5 violation) and cost a call per write, whereas regex+heuristic is deterministic (same bytes → same edges) and free, so the graph grows on every write. The READ side (os/usr/lib/holo/q/holo-q-recall.js) is HYBRID(vector ⊕ BM25) → RRF → a 1-hop typed-graph EXPAND (a chunk co-citing a top hit's link target joins — the +P@5 lift from the SovereignAI/GBrain sweep, the load-bearing step the hybrid ranking alone misses) → an OPTIONAL synthesize step (a cited answer + an honest GAP analysis; with no synth bound it returns null, NEVER a faked answer, L5). The deterministic core (retrieve→fuse→expand) runs ZERO models and re-derives byte-for-byte; synthesize is opt-in and the only model call. The whole retrieval seals ONE re-derivable holoq:RecallReceipt (mintRecallReceipt): prov:used = the retrieved chunk κs (tagged with rank + which retriever) AND the edge κs the walk traversed, prov:generated = the answer κ (synthesize) or the result-set κ (retrieve) — a single altered byte (a chunk κ, an edge κ, the mode, the conscience verdict) breaks the address and is refused (L5, canonicalization reused from ADR-0090 holo-q-receipt.mjs). Wired as Q.recall / Q.configureRecall (holo-q.js); with no corpus configured it returns an honest notice and never throws, like Q.ask/Q.fuse; an unchanged re-index is a no-op κ and editing one page re-chunks only that page (the near-repeat property). HONEST: PGLite (GBrain's WASM-Postgres) is NOT adopted — the κ-store IS the store (L4), the retrieval MODEL is borrowed not the database; the +31 P@5 figure is GBrain's, the witness proves the MECHANISM (graph-expand pulls in a co-citing chunk the hybrid ranking ranked below k) not that exact number; the auto-link graph trades recall on ambiguous entities for determinism + zero cost, which the read-time synth step backstops. Witnessed 40/40 (tools/holo-q-recall-witness.mjs: deterministic chunking + zero-LLM auto-link extraction · index builds vector+BM25+graph all content-addressed · hybrid retrieval (BM25 exact-term + vector semantic) · RRF agreement-ranks · the graph EXPAND pulls in a co-citing chunk the hybrid missed and disabling expand drops it · the deterministic core ran ZERO generative models · repeat → identical result-set κ · the RecallReceipt re-derives + a tampered receipt refused · no-op re-index + single-page re-chunk on edit · synthesize binds a cited answer + gaps and is an honest null with none bound · the door Q.recall is governed/honest + describe lists the verb · entity κ is content-addressed/normalized). Two fold-ins recorded for later (not in this row): a SOMATIC conscience axis (hardware can-sustain pre-flight) at the next conscience touch, and lite-parse WASM ingestion as a Forge κ-transform once a corpus is worth feeding. Pending: the os-closure.json κ-pin for the new served modules (the deferred re-lock cascade, the same step ADR-0098/0097 defer — SW network-fallback, never 409s); shell configureRecall wiring onto the warm corpus; the Omni bar surfacing private results behind the open-web ones."
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
          "@id": "earl:passed"
        }
      },
      "earl:mode": {
        "@id": "earl:automatic"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "earl:Assertion",
      "earl:assertedBy": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/tools/gate"
      },
      "earl:subject": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os",
        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-import",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Import (ADR-0092/0093) — paste a GitHub URL → a running, content-addressed Holo app, 100% serverless. Import is a DETERMINISTIC ENCODER onto the existing publishSource/Q spine, classified by build-locus (static/SPA → DIRECT inlined into one self-contained app κ; client-bundle → FORGE, a real esbuild κ-transform — esbuild INJECTED, deterministic so the bundle re-derives, κ-parity with a studio-built app; SSR/backend/DB/CLI → out-of-scope-v1, the reason SURFACED, never a fake app). An imported app's κ EQUALS repo.publishSource for identical bytes (first-class); a re-import is O(1) (κ-memo, re-fetches nothing); a flipped byte → a different κ, refused (L5); the receipt walks to git+repo@commit forever; unserved external/dependency refs are named. The build tool is VENDORED + κ-pinned (esbuild-wasm, local-first + re-derived against the committed pin before use, no trusted CDN). The network is a GOVERNED INGEST BOUNDARY (Law L4): every outbound fetch (repo bytes, a CDN dep) passes the conscience BEFORE it happens — a red-line P5 PII URL / ungranted host is REFUSED and the network is never touched; an accepted fetch mints a re-derivable hosc:Ingest receipt; fail-closed. Witnessed tools/holo-import-witness.mjs (38/38: parse · classify the classes truthfully · byte-faithful inline · external refs surfaced · imported κ === publishSource κ · re-import re-derives · tamper refused · receipt pins git+commit · O(1) on the Q spine + re-fetches nothing · governed ingest: fail-closed, host-opt-in+receipt, accept, PII→P5 block w/ network untouched) + tools/holo-forge-bundle-witness.mjs (12/12, REAL esbuild) + tools/holo-forge-vendor-witness.mjs (6/6, the vendored toolchain re-derives, tamper refused); verified live in the booted shell."
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
          "@id": "earl:passed"
        }
      },
      "earl:mode": {
        "@id": "earl:automatic"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "earl:Assertion",
      "earl:assertedBy": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/tools/gate"
      },
      "earl:subject": {
