        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-import-agent",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Import → agent-native (ADR-0093) — the moment a GitHub repo imports it is auto-WIRED into the MCP + /~<app>/api REST seams every holospace ALREADY exposes, so any AI agent or holo app can fetch · re-derive (L5) · run · share · discover it with ZERO author effort. Agent-native = DERIVING one manifest + one resolver that mount the app into seams that already work (holo-mcp + holo-api over one κ-store): BASELINE exposes the app source as a self-verifying RESOURCE + the universal verbs + a NANDA AgentFacts record; the DECLARED-surface tier projects a repo's OpenAPI/typed-exports interface into faithfully-schema'd MCP tools. EXPOSURE ≠ AUTHORIZATION throughout: a projected egress tool is discoverable but DEFAULT-DENY — callable only through the conscience-gated governed-egress boundary (a granted call fills path/query/body + seals a hosc:Egress receipt; ungranted → refused, network untouched). The SERVERLESS TRANSPORT BRIDGE makes an in-memory import reachable by an EXTERNAL HTTP agent through the Service Worker (the page writes its manifest + κ-objects into the holo-imports cache the SW reads) — /~<id>/mcp + /~<id>/api answer with no origin server. Witnessed tools/holo-import-agent-witness.mjs (53/53, against the REAL holo-mcp + holo-mcp-core + holo-api-core + holo-object cores: app-scoped MCP server · resources/read + REST GET /o/<κ> re-derive L5 · capability card self-verifies · ONE resolver serves MCP+REST · tamper→verify-false + REST 404 · AgentFacts self-verifies + lineage · DECLARED OpenAPI→faithful tools + egress execution callable-when-granted/refused-when-not + receipt · SW bridge entry-contract · baseline grants no capability · deterministic/O(1)); verified live in the booted shell (external HTTP agent reaches an import; a declared tool default-denies then executes a real governed egress after grant)."
      },
      "earl:result": {
        "@type": "earl:TestResult",
        "earl:outcome": {
          "@id": "earl:passed"
        }
      },
      "earl:mode": {
        "@id": "earl:automatic"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "earl:Assertion",
      "earl:assertedBy": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/tools/gate"
      },
      "earl:subject": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os",
        "dcterms:title": "Hologram OS"
      },
      "earl:test": {
        "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-hub",
        "dcterms:title": "Holo Hub (ADR-0094) — a Shopify-class store for the κ-addressed universe, 100% serverless and in-tab. A PRODUCT IS a holo app addressed by its did:holo κ; the apps/index.jsonld catalog IS the product feed. Built by ADOPTING Medusa's commerce model as a byte-pinned spec (ADR-0029 'adopt the desktop, don't run it') — NOT running Medusa's Node+Postgres server. holo-hub.mjs maps each catalog app to a Medusa StoreProduct-shaped UOR κ-object (product = app by κ, bound to the pinned Store-API spec κ), persisted over the κ-store (the Postgres replacement); witnessed tools/holo-hub-witness.mjs (catalog → product set with κ identity, bijection/no-orphan, L5 round-trip, tamper refused, deterministic, 0-network). The store renders in a sealed in-tab holospace (apps/hub/index.html — editorial Today, category grids, product=κ cards with live in-tab κ re-derivation, one-tap Open renders the LIVE app via Scene, store-in-store nesting incl. true Hub-in-Hub) for both people and AI agents."
      },
